This article is a statement by the President on the arrest of Ratko Mladic, who was responsible for ordering the execution of 8,000 unarmed men and boys in Srebrencia 15 years ago. The President applauds the efforts of President Tadic and the Government of Serbia in finding Mladic and ensuring that he faces justice. The President also expresses the importance of international justice and the United States' commitment to it, as well as the commitment to supporting reconciliation efforts in the Balkans and preventing future atrocities. The President hopes that the arrest brings solace to the families of Mladic's victims and strengthens the ties among the people of the region.